## ðŸ” Privacy-Preserving Computation

A central concept explored in this thesis is **Homomorphic Encryption**.

This cryptographic technique allows computations to be performed directly on **encrypted data**, meaning:
- raw data is never exposed to the cloud,
- processing can be outsourced securely,
- only authorized parties can decrypt the results.

While promising, homomorphic encryption introduces strong constraints that significantly impact how data analysis algorithms can be designed and executed.


```mermaid
flowchart LR
    
    subgraph Client
        direction LR
        subgraph RC[ ]
            ERc[Encrypted Results] -->|Decrypt| R[Plain Results]
        end
        subgraph DC[ ]
            D[Plain Data] -->|Encrypt| EDc[Encrypted Data]
        end
    end
subgraph Cloud
        direction TB
        subgraph Dcloud[ ]
            EDcl[Encrypted Data]
        end
        subgraph Rcloud[ ]
            ERcl[Encrypted Results]
        end
        Dcloud -->|Encrypted Computation| Rcloud
    end
    
   DC -->|Send Encrypted Data| Dcloud
   Rcloud -->|Send Encrypted Results| RC

```



